Also, it's probably good to assume that if you're going to be entering
your pass phrase, you're going to be working with (potentially) sensitive
information.. either sending it out, or recieving it, in which case you're
likely to have kicked anyone with Over-The-Shoulder disease out of the
room.

I know I do.

the only potential good thing about not being able to see the password on
the screen is that it couldn't be snooped with a passive emmisions device.

I know my keyboard makes rf noise whenever I press a key tho.. i dont know
if it's distinguishable or not.  probably is, if you've got good enough
equipment... different scan codes probably produce subtally different
RF signatures..

but even then, i figure if someone's going thru THAT much trouble to read
my data then i'm in deep kemshi anyway and it's probably not going to help
me much that my pass phrase can't be seen on the screen.


